This dish ended up amazing because of one simple modification: added one pecorini pepper. It made the flavor so much more complex. I also used white wine instead of chicken broth, and sauteed the chicken in rosemary and garlic. I didn't end up needing cheese in the end, but I did add a bit of salt. Next time though, I'll be less inpatient and actually let the fettuccine cook all the way through.

