Rating: 3
Delicious. I tasted the dish before adding the cheese, and decided to serve with a few lumps of goat cheese instead of the jack. It melted in, contributing to the creaminess and adding a nice tang that worked well with the smoky heat of the chipotles. I used 2% milk with cornstarch, reduced, instead of the cream, as well - so that, with the goat cheese, had the added benefit of making it a lower-fat dish.

Rating: 3
A lot of reviewers had issues with the fat. An effective & delicious way to replace cream is to use evaporated milk. Choose from non to low to whole. It pretty much keeps the body provided by cream, just less fat. Adding a splash of cream is help balance the flavors and is always good. Another issue is the chipotle. Chipotles ARE smoky! They are roasted jalapenos! Use chipotles in adobo, just rinse off the sauce if you don't like the taste. Finally, the best way to assemble is to add cream sauce to pasta, add cheese & stir until well mixed, then add veggies & meat. There are so many ways to alter this dish to meet your taste or to use the leftovers calling from the fridge.

