This was delicious and easy to prepare, and not remotely bland. Don't cut back on the cilantro, as it is so fabulous with the chicken and red peppers and onions. Recipe as written is easy to make, and having omitted the poblano chiles for lack thereof (sub'd crushed red pepper), this was PLENTY spicy. Granted, I wasn't looking for a "southwestern" dish, just something yummy to make with chicken, pasta, red onion, red pepper and garlic; it was quick and great. HOWEVER, I could not imagine making this with 2 cups of cream -- turning an otherwise healthy dish into a heart-attack on a plate -- so I reduced a cup of 1% milk and a cup of chicken broth for a bit, and it was DEVINE. Tweak it a bit with common sense, and ENJOY!

