Rating: 3
This was great. I used a white onion and threw in some sliced zucchini - both just fine. Instead of cream, I used 1% milk mixed with 2 Tbsp. cornstarch and that worked great. The poblano chili I added was mild, but those can be hot. We liked the amount of heat. Regarding the chipotle - to store, I simply put the remainder of the can in a clean glass jar (8 - 10 oz.) and tape the can's label around the outside of the jar. Better than Boullion jars are a good size. The chipotles keep in excess of a year in the refrigerator - I never let fingers touch the chilis or the adobado sauce.

