Rating: 3
This is an excellent "adult" dish. It was a bit too spicy for my 10 year old. She said "It's very good Mom, but it's too spicy for me. It isn't hot like hot sauce, just too spicy." She tought I had put too much black pepper in it. For a family meal, you might want to substitute a dash of hot sauce for the chipotle peppers in the sauce. If you know of a milder pepper, use it. I also made the salad with cucumber and pineapple in simple syrup type dressing. The sweet helps cool down the heat from the peppers. My husband and I both get indigestion and heartburn fairly often, but this didn't cause either of us to have stomach discomfort. In the hour that the chicken marinated, I did the rest of the slicing, etc., got the pasta water boiling, and prepared garlic bread for the broiler. Dinner on the table in about an hour and 20 minutes. I would definitely make it again.